The paper deals with a graph representation problem for interval graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem also involves the recognition of certain graph classes, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper mentions applications in biology and temporal graphs, which could potentially fall under the categories of graph theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
